## 6. Styling Approach

### Methodology: CSS Modules
- Every component has a co-located `.module.css` file
- No global CSS framework (no Tailwind, no styled-components)
- Class names are locally scoped via CSS Modules

### Style File Pattern

```css
/* ComponentName.module.css */
.root {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  /* Use px values matching Figma exactly */
  width: 360px;
  height: 52px;
  border-radius: 26px;
  /* Use hardcoded hex colors from Figma */
  background-color: #074ED8;
  color: #FFFFFF;
  /* Typography */
  font-family: 'Pretendard', sans-serif;
  font-size: 18px;
  font-weight: 700;
}
```

### Key Styling Rules

1. **Units**: Use `px` for all fixed dimensions (matching Figma)
2. **Colors**: Use hex values directly from Figma (prefer CSS variables for consistency, but raw hex is also used)
3. **No responsive design**: Fixed 393x852 viewport
4. **Global styles**: Only resets and base typography in `src/styles/global.css`
5. **Large pages**: Split into multiple CSS files (e.g., `Home-1.module.css`, `Home-2.module.css`)

### Figma Auto Layout → CSS Flexbox Mapping

| Figma Property | CSS Equivalent |
|----------------|---------------|
| Auto Layout (Horizontal) | `display: flex; flex-direction: row;` |
| Auto Layout (Vertical) | `display: flex; flex-direction: column;` |
| Gap: Auto | `justify-content: space-between;` |
| Gap: `N` | `gap: Npx;` |
| Packed (Start) | `justify-content: flex-start;` |
| Packed (Center) | `justify-content: center;` |
| Packed (End) | `justify-content: flex-end;` |
| Space Between | `justify-content: space-between;` |
| Align: Top | `align-items: flex-start;` |
| Align: Center | `align-items: center;` |
| Align: Bottom | `align-items: flex-end;` |
| Fill Container (width) | `width: 100%;` or `flex: 1;` |
| Hug Contents | `width: fit-content;` |

